mp to search</a>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<table class=\"prettytable\" style=\"margin: 0;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\" style=\"font-size:larger;\"><span class=\"nhsym clr-cyan\">[</span> &#8194; tower shield &#8194;\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Appearance\n</th>\n<td>tower shield\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Slot\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Shield\" title=\"Shield\">shield</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>AC\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Armor_class\" title=\"Armor class\">3</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Special\n</th>\n<td><i>(none)</i>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Base price\n</th>\n<td>20 <a href=\"/wiki/Zorkmid\" title=\"Zorkmid\">zm</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Weight\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Weight\" title=\"Weight\">200</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Material\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Iron\" title=\"Iron\">iron</a>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n</div>\n<p>The <b>tower shield</b> is a type of <a href=\"/wiki/Shield\" title=\"Shield\">shield</a> that appears in <i><a href=\"/wiki/DNetHack\" title=\"DNetHack\">dNetHack</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/SpliceHack\" title=\"SpliceHack\">SpliceHack</a></i>, and <i><a href=\"/wiki/Hack%27EM\" title=\"Hack&#39;EM\">Hack'EM</a></i>. It provides <a href=\"/wiki/AC\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"AC\">AC</a> 3 when worn.\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/DNetHack\" title=\"DNetHack\">dNetHack</a> the tower shield provides 4AC (and 0 DR, like all shields), and grants <a href=\"/wiki/Magic_cancellation\" title=\"Magic cancellation\">MC1</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Strategy\">Strategy</span></h2>\n<p>The tower shield provides the most AC of any shield, but unfortunately it also weighs the most. It also inhibits spellcasting like other metallic shields.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span></h2>\n\n<!-- \nNe